PROJECT CONTEXT:
This is a Next.js 13+ (App Router) full-stack school management system.

Tech stack:
- Next.js (App Router)
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- NextAuth for authentication
- SQLite (app.db)
- API routes inside /app/api

Existing structure:
- Role-based dashboards:
  - /dashboard/admin
  - /dashboard/teacher
  - /dashboard/student
  - /dashboard/institution
- Admin APIs already exist under:
  /app/api/admin/*
    - users
    - pending-teachers
    - pending-courses
    - approve/reject APIs
    - dashboard stats

OBJECTIVE:
Enhance and build a COMPLETE ADMIN PANEL with professional UI + full functionality.

ADMIN PANEL REQUIREMENTS:

1. DASHBOARD (/dashboard/admin)
- Show stats cards:
  - Total Users
  - Total Students
  - Total Teachers
  - Total Courses
  - Pending Approvals
- Add charts (use chart library like recharts or chart.js):
  - User growth
  - Course creation trends

2. USER MANAGEMENT (/dashboard/admin/users)
- Table with:
  - Name
  - Email
  - Role (student/teacher/admin)
  - Status (active/pending)
- Features:
  - Search + filter
  - Delete user
  - Change role
  - Activate/Deactivate

3. COURSE MANAGEMENT (/dashboard/admin/courses)
- Show all courses
- Approve / Reject courses
- View course details
- Delete course

4. APPROVAL SYSTEM (/dashboard/admin/approvals)
- Pending teachers
- Pending courses
- Approve / Reject buttons
- Show details before approval

5. UI/UX IMPROVEMENTS
- Use reusable components from /components/ui
- Add:
  - Sidebar navigation (Admin only)
  - Top navbar
  - Loading skeletons
  - Toast notifications
  - Modal dialogs for actions

6. SECURITY
- Protect admin routes using NextAuth
- Only allow role === "admin"

7. API INTEGRATION
- Use existing APIs:
  - /api/admin/users
  - /api/admin/pending-teachers
  - /api/admin/pending-courses
  - /api/admin/approve-*
  - /api/admin/reject-*
- If missing, generate new APIs

8. CODE STYLE
- Use clean, modular components
- Follow existing folder structure
- Use server + client components properly
- Use TypeScript types from /lib/types

9. BONUS FEATURES (if possible)
- Pagination for tables
- Export data (CSV)
- Admin profile section
- Activity logs

OUTPUT FORMAT:
- Generate:
  1. Updated pages inside /app/(dashboard)/admin/*
  2. New reusable components if needed
  3. API improvements if required
  4. Clean, production-ready code

IMPORTANT:
Do NOT rewrite the entire project.
Only enhance and extend the ADMIN PANEL using the existing structure.